body:
> below is a result on windows7 64bit.

This is strange. I would expect you to display many 15.6252ms (just like my computer). But it is possible that other program (not built by go1.6) is called timeBeginPeriod and is still runinng. This will make your PC timer run at 1ms. Until last program that called timeBeginPeriod exits. See https://randomascii.wordpress.com/2013/07/08/windows-timer-resolution-megawatts-wasted/ for details.

Alex
